   <body>
      <prereq>
         <ul>
            <li>At least one saved filter exists. <ph product="Exclude_PG_Content">For information on saving a filter, refer to <xref href="SaveFltr.xml">Saving a Filter</xref>.</ph>
            </li>
         </ul>
      </prereq>
      <context>The following procedure describes the steps to use a pre-defined filter. The <uicontrol>PROJECTS</uicontrol> list page is used here as an example.</context>
      <ol>
         <li>
            <p>In the module menu, click <uicontrol>Projects</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The list of projects you are invited to is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the tool bar, click <image href="../../Icons/Filter-Toolbar.png" placement="inline">
                  <alt>Filter</alt>
               </image>.</p>
            <p>The <uicontrol>FILTERS</uicontrol> dialog box is displayed.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>In the <uicontrol>Select Filter</uicontrol> section, select the appropriate filter.</p>
            <p>Available options are filters defined for the page. <ph product="Exclude_PG_Content">For information on defining a filter, refer to <xref href="SaveFltr.xml">Saving a Filter</xref>.</ph>
            </p>
            <p>
               <fig>
                  <title>Select Filter</title>
                  <image href="../Screenshots/Pre-defined_Filter.jpg" placement="inline"/>
               </fig>
            </p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Click <uicontrol>Apply Filter</uicontrol>.</p>
            <p>The filter is applied, and the color of the filter icon <image width=".5cm" href="../../Icons/Blue_Filter.jpg" placement="inline">
                  <alt>Filter</alt>
               </image> in the toolbar is turned blue.</p>
         </li>
         <li>
            <p>Optionally, to clear the filter, in the tool bar, click <image width=".5cm" href="../../Icons/Blue_Filter.jpg" placement="inline">
                  <alt>Filter</alt>
               </image>, and then click <uicontrol>Clear Filter</uicontrol>.</p>
         </li>
      </ol>
      <result/>
